.TH "cipso_v4_genopt" 9 "cipso_v4_genopt" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
cipso_v4_genopt \- Generate a CIPSO option
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" cipso_v4_genopt
.BI "(unsigned char *buf "  ","
.BI "u32 buf_len "  ","
.BI "const struct cipso_v4_doi *doi_def "  ","
.BI "const struct netlbl_lsm_secattr *secattr "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "buf" 12
the option buffer
.IP "buf_len" 12
the size of opt_buf
.IP "doi_def" 12
the CIPSO DOI to use
.IP "secattr" 12
the security attributes
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Generate a CIPSO option using the DOI definition and security attributes
passed to the function.  Returns the length of the option on success and
negative values on failure.
